widgets_values: Grabs only the interpolated frames from the mini batch and then puts them between the last and first frame at the end of the main batch to combine for a smoother interpolated loop
A mini batch of the last and first frame in reverse order
embedding:BadDream, embedding:UnrealisticDream, nsfw, nude, texts, human, woman, boy, man, girl, letters, words, (worst quality, low quality:1.4)

One of the problems with interpolated loop videos is that when it repeats, there's a small jitter when going back to beginning, this happens because frames are missing between the last and first frame and the higher the interpolation, the more pronounced the jitter is.

I created this workflow to help with that by taking your video and interpolating the last frame with the first frame and putting it all back together at the end, creating a smoother interpolated loop.

All you need to do is select your video mode and enable or disable the FILM node depending on the source video you're using. If using a RAW video, select 1 and enable FILM node (this is default).
If using an already interpolated video, select 2 and disable the FILM node, also select the same Interpolation Multiplier used for the source, so that it evenly blends the frames at the end.

The workflow defaults to 2x on the green "Interpolation Multiplier" node, but 3x and 4x are also supported.

A note about FILM vs RIFE: Although RIFE is faster, FILM creates much smoother and accurately detailed interpolated frames, which is why it takes longer, but the results are worth the wait.

There are image save nodes around the workflow you can enable if you'd like to see the process and difference of the smoother loop.
